uì™T<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";a:2:{i:36;O:8:"stdClass":11:{s:7:"term_id";i:36;s:4:"name";s:9:"Community";s:4:"slug";s:9:"community";s:10:"term_group";i:0;s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";i:36;s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:336:"We will present communities and organizations that matter and make a different in the scene, with meetings, gatherings during festivals, great for resources and courses, places that are great for connecting with other artists, and even companies working with creative technologies launching revolutionary products and tools just for us.";s:6:"parent";i:62;s:5:"count";i:3;s:9:"object_id";i:3750;s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:62;O:8:"stdClass":11:{s:7:"term_id";i:62;s:4:"name";s:8:"Learning";s:4:"slug";s:8:"learning";s:10:"term_group";i:0;s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";i:62;s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:2255:"With technologies constantly evolving even the pros are learning new things all the time, isn't this what makes the VJ scene interesting and challenging at the same time. In this category you'll find a diversity of information in posts: to get up and started, everything to feed your brains thirst, or to perfect your skills and explore more technics or methods, and become knowledgeable on those complex tools that we use to make audio visual art and installations. On each page you'll notice drop down bars displayed  just over the posts to quickly find what you are looking for without browsing every page. You can explore <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/books/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Books</span></a> by subject or tool of choice and even select by author, in <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/community/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Community</span></a> you can read articles about organizations playing a role in the VJ scene and even in the industry, make sure to network and support to really get out there. Not sure where to start? No fears we've all been there, in <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/education/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Education</span></a> there is degrees you might want to consider or/and if that's not an option there are courses available for anyone to register. <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/freeware/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Freeware,</span></a> free goodies! yup that's right, all of them and that's not all, in <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/open-source-code/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Open Source</span></a> with it's full flexibility, is what you coding creatives and hacking lunatics are looking for, updates on the the latest geeky stuff out there, well at least we'll make sure it's up to date for you. Budget sometimes limits our options, well guess what? developers of those great live software you use, they made lot's of <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/tutorials/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Tutorials</span></a> just for you so you can get a hold of it, and if that's not enough there are <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/tag/workshops/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Workshops</span></a> you might want to follow in a city near you.
